#how-to-modal.modal.fade aria-hidden="true" aria-labelledby="course-title" role="dialog" tabindex="-1"
  .modal-dialog
    .modal-content
      .modal-header
        h3 How to use the Scheduler Generator
      .modal-body    
        .panel-group#accordion
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
                h4.panel-title
                  a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne" Adding Courses             
            #collapseOne.panel-collapse.collapse.in
              .panel-body
                ul
                  li There are 2 ways to get courses into the scheduler.
                  ol
                    li Using the search bar on the right. Search for a course you're thinking of taking. You will then be prompted to choose the sections you can take. These sections will be used to generate your possible options.
                    li When browsing through the rest of theCourseForum. If you find a course you want to take, simply click the "Save Course" button. This course will then appear in your saved courses when you visit the scheduler.
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
                h4.panel-title
                  a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseTwo" Generating Schedules                
            #collapseTwo.panel-collapse.collapse
                .panel-body
                  ul
                    li Once you've added the courses you want, clicking the generate button will construct all possible combinations of the sections you've selected. 
                    li If this is overwhelming, you can try "Generate with Options" which will attempt to narrow down your possible schedules based on your preferences.
                    li You can view all the generated schedules using the blue slider. Drag the handle, or click it and use your arrow keys to see the possible permutations. 
          .panel.panel-default
            .panel-heading
                h4.panel-title
                  a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseThree" Managing Schedules
            #collapseThree.panel-collapse.collapse
                .panel-body                
                  ul
                    li When you find a schedule you particularly like, you can save it with the "Save" button so that you can revist it later.
                    li You can revisit your saved schedules with the "Load" button.
                    li Once you have finalized a schedule. You can use the "Export" button to download your schedule as an .ics file.          
                    a href="https://support.google.com/calendar/answer/37118?hl=en" 
                      li For instructions on how to import this into Google Calendar, see here          
                    a href="https://support.apple.com/kb/PH11524?locale=en_US" 
                      li For instructions on how to import this into iCal see here.
      .modal-footer
        button.btn.btn-primary data-dismiss="modal" type="button"  Got it!